cscie97.asn4.ecommerce.product

Class Application

  • java.lang.Object
    • cscie97.asn4.ecommerce.product.Content
      • cscie97.asn4.ecommerce.product.Application

  • public class Application
extends Content
    Represents an Application in the Mobile Application Store. Applications are Content items, but have an additional property - they have a file size expressed in bytes. Each Application item that lives in the Product catalog is a unique item. Application items may be added to the Product catalog and made publicly searchable; those use cases are supported by means of the IProductAPI.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    David Killeffer <rayden7@gmail.com>
    See Also:
    ProductAPI, Content, ContentSearch, Ringtone, Wallpaper

        Class constructor. Uses primary constructor from Content to set nearly all object properties, except for the Application-specific fileSizeBytes.
        Parameters:
        id - the unique content ID
        name - the content item name
        description - content item description
        authorName - content author's name
        rating - the current rating of the content item
        categories - list of categories the content item belongs to
        devices - all the unique Device objects that the content item is compatible with
        price - price of the content in BitCoins
        allowedInCountries - list of Country objects where the content may be downloaded
        supportedLanguages - list of 5-character supported language codes
        imageURL - a string to a public URL image of the content
        type - the ContentType of the item
        fileSizeBytes - the size of the application file (in bytes)

      • validateContent

        public static boolean validateContent(Application content)
        Public static method that checks that all required fields are set, and that all content item values are valid (e.g., ratings are 0 to 5, where 5 is best, item price should only allow positive numbers, etc.). For Application objects, a valid filesize in bytes is required.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        true if all properties are valid, false otherwise

      • hashCode

        public int hashCode()
        Since Application objects may be added to collections, and also since the IProductAPI enforces that all Application items be unique, this method provides a way to get the unique hash code for the current content item. Uses the Apache Commons HashCodeBuilder to generate a unique hash code for the current item based on two randomly chosen unique prime numbers and all the object properties.
        Overrides:
        hashCode in class Content
        Returns:
        a unique integer hash code for this particular object

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object compare)
        Since Application objects may be added to collections, and also since the IProductAPI enforces that all Application items be unique, this method provides a way to determine if another Application item is the same as the current one. Uses the Apache Commons EqualsBuilder to determine if the two objects are indeed equal to each other.
